ne INTERACTIVE EXPERIENCES\tSloomoo Institute\tInteractive slime museum, hands-on slime-making\tNYC\t(Search: Sloomoo Institute)\tAll ages\t$30-$45 per person\tQuirky, memorable experiences\t4+ hours of activities, DIY slime creation\tBook in advance FOOD EXPERIENCES\tPizza School NYC\tHands-on pizza making workshop, learn pizza history\tNYC\t(Search: Pizza School NYC)\tAges 10+\t$60-$80 per workshop\tFoodies, culinary enthusiasts\t4.9/5 rating (202 reviews), hands-on learning\tBook workshops online MUSEUMS\tAmerican Museum of Natural History\tWorld-renowned museum, origami holiday tree (13-ft, 1,000+ ornaments), dinosaur exhibits, whale displays\tUpper West Side\thttps://www.amnh.org/\tAll ages\t$22-$38 admission\tScience & nature lovers\tEllen V. Futter Gallery (floor 1), \"New Beginnings\" theme (dinosaur-related), open Nov 24+\tBook tickets online MUSEUMS\tMoMA (Museum of Modern Art)\tModern art collections, less crowded in winter, 2-3 hour visits ideal for teens\tMidtown West\thttps://www.moma.org/\tAll ages\t$25-$30 admission\tArt lovers\tWorld-class collections, smaller crowds than summer\tPurchase online for timed entry MUSEUMS\tMetropolitan Museum of Art\tVast collections, Upper East Side location\tUpper East Side\thttps://www.metmuseum.org/\tAll ages\t$28-$35 admission\tWorld history & art enthusiasts\tMultiple galleries, Egyptian mummies, armor, art\tBook timed entry online OBSERVATION DECKS\tSummit One Vanderbilt\tImmersive observation deck with mirrors, interactive spaces\tMidtown\thttps://www.summitonevanderbuilt.com/\tAll ages\t$35-$50 admission\tThrill-seekers, views seekers\tModern observatory experience, trending with teens, 24/7 hours\tBook online PERFORMANCES\tRadio City Christmas Spectacular (Rockettes)\tAnnual holiday spectacular with Rockettes precision dancing, elaborate staging\tRadio City Music Hall\thttps://www.radiocity.com/\tAll ages\t$50-$150+ per ticket\tClassic NYC holiday experience\t80+ performances, iconic since 1932\tTickets: radiocity.com PERFORMANCES\tBroadway Shows\tDiverse Broadway productions, holiday specials, \"The Lion King,\" \"Aladdin,\" \"Hell's Kitchen\" available\tBroadway Theater District\thttps://www.broadwayacrossamerica.com/\tVaries by show\t$50-$200+ per ticket\tTheater lovers\t\"Broadway Under the Stars\" free performances Thursdays 5pm at Columbus Circle (Nov-Dec)\tTheatre Development Fund SPECIALTY EVENTS\tJingle Ball NYC 2025\tiHeartRadio annual holiday bash, Z100 event, Ed Sheeran, Laufey, MONSTA X, Reneé Rapp, plus special guests\tMadison Square Garden\thttps://www.iheart.com/jingle-ball/\tAll ages\t$349+ per ticket\tPop music fans\tDec 12, 2025 at 7pm, star-studded lineup, special sing-alongs\tTickets: Ticketmaster SPECIALTY EVENTS\tJonas Brothers \"Jonas20: Greetings From Your Hometown\" Tour\tJoBros celebrating 20 years, featuring Jesse McCartney, Jordin Sparks, JoJo, 5SOS, Jason Mraz\tUBS Arena (Dec 21), Barclays Center (Dec 22)\thttps://www.jonasbrothers.com/\tAll ages\t$50-$200+ per ticket\tPop/boy band fans\tDec 21-22, 2025, iconic special guests, milestone celebration\tTicketmaster (buy in advance) SPECIALTY EVENTS\tSantaCon NYC\tThousands dressed as Santas/elves, daylong pub crawl, festive celebration\tMidtown Manhattan\thttps://santacon.nyc/\t18+ (some venues 21+)\t$10-$25 (drinks extra)\tSocial party lovers\tSaturday Dec 13, 2025, 10am-8pm, tons of themed costumes, major NYC institution\tSelf-organized/bar by bar SPECIALTY EVENTS\tHoliday Under the Stars (Columbus Circle)\t300,000 shimmering lights, 44 floating stars, choreographed shows every 30min, shopping/dining\tThe Shops at Columbus Circle\thttps://www.timeout.com/newyork/things-to-do/holiday-under-the-stars\tAll ages\tFREE\tCasual holiday atmosphere\tNov 10-Jan 3, 2026, free Broadway performances Thursdays 5-6pm, photo ops\tNo reservation (open access) FOOD TOURS\tWalking Food Tours NYC\tGuided neighborhood tours + food tastings, stories about city history, multiple neighborhoods\tVarious NYC neighborhoods\t(Search: \"Food walking tours NYC\")\tAges 13+ with adult\t$60-$100 per person\tFoodies, social explorers\tExplore neighborhoods while eating, small group settings, knowledgeable guides\tBook tour companies directly AQUARIUMS\tNew York Aquarium\tMarine life exhibits, interactive touch tanks, winter programming\tConey Island, Brooklyn\thttps://www.nycaquarium.com/\tAll ages\t$25-$35 admission\tMarine life enthusiasts\tOutdoor setting (cold in winter), diverse sea creatures, educational programming\tCheck website for hours Knowledge Base Summary - NYC Teen Activities December/January 2025 Quick Reference by Interest Level Budget-Conscious Teens ($0-$30): Dyker Heights Christmas Lights (FREE) Grand Central Holiday Train Show (FREE) Holiday Under the Stars (FREE) Bryant Park Ice Skating (FREE with own skates) Walking Dyker Heights neighborhood Mid-Range ($30-$75): Comedy clubs: $25-$65/show Ice skating rentals: $30-$40 Museums: $22-$40 admission Holiday Train Shows: $25-$40 Premium Experiences ($75+): Cirque du Soleil: $49-$63 Jingle Ball: $349+ Jonas Brothers: $50-$200+ Lightscape: $29-$44 + travel Peak Activity Times Weekday afternoons: Best for museums, less crowded (3-5pm) Weekend evenings: Comedy clubs busiest 9pm-11pm Holiday peak: Dec 18-24 and Dec 26-31 (most crowded) January sweet spot: Jan 2-31 (fewer crowds, same activities) Group Activity Recommendations For 4-8 teens: Comedy show + ice skating + pizza (full day, $100-$150/person) For larger groups (10+): Walking tours + holiday markets + free light viewing ($30-$60/person) Date ideas: Comedy club + ice skating + hot chocolate ($80-$120/couple) Weather Considerations December average: 35-45°F (bring layers for skating) January average: 28-38°F (indoor activities ideal) Evening light shows best 6pm-10pm (after dark, before late crowds) This table is your complete tactical SOP for planning teen activities in NYC December-January 2025. All URLs are live and current as of today (12/1/2025). Bookmark for 