ns@parks.nyc.gov OR visit local recreation center to register\tEnvironmental education, community service opportunities, leadership skills, certificate programs, meet other teens\tYear-round (register by December for winter programs)\tYES - group programs\tVaries (ongoing program)\tINPUT: Teen interest in environment + commitment level REQUEST OUTPUT: Free enrollment in Green Teen program + environmental education + community service hours FREE YOUTH PROGRAMS\tNYC Parks - RECYouth Digital Media Program\tFree video/audio production learning, teens create content, develop technical skills\tMultiple locations citywide\thttps://www.nycgovparks.org/programs/recreation/teens\tFREE (registration required)\tVisit NYC Parks website to find location + register\tLearn filmmaking, audio production, digital media skills, create real projects, portfolio building\tYear-round (register in advance)\tYES - cohort-based learning\tSemester-based programs\tINPUT: Teen creative interest + registration REQUEST OUTPUT: Free enrollment + digital media training + portfolio projects FREE YOUTH PROGRAMS\tYMCA Teen Night Out (TNO)\tFree comprehensive youth development program for ages 13-18, activities + classes + field trips\tMultiple YMCA locations\thttps://ymcanyc.org/programs/kids-family/teen-programs\tFREE\tRegister at local YMCA or online\tSports, arts, academics, field trips, mentoring, safe community space, evening programs\tEvenings & weekends\tYES - group-based community program\tOngoing weekly programs\tINPUT: Teen age 13-18 + YMCA membership (some free options available) REQUEST OUTPUT: Free/low-cost enrollment + weekly programming + peer community BUDGET-FRIENDLY UNDER $10\tWinter Jam (NYC Parks)\tFree winter sports festival, Central Park, sledding, ice skating demos, food vendors\tCentral Park\thttps://www.nycgovparks.org/reg/winter-jam\tFREE (optional vendor food purchases $5-15)\tNo registration needed, walk-in event\tWinter sports activities, games, seasonal celebrations, sledding hills, ice skating exhibition, hot drinks available\tWinter weekends (check NYC Parks calendar for 2025-26 dates)\tYES - festival atmosphere\t2-4 hours\tINPUT: Group of teens interested in winter sports REQUEST OUTPUT: Free festival access + winter activities + demo participation BUDGET-FRIENDLY UNDER $10\tFree Museum Fridays (Various Museums)\tFirst Friday of each month: many museums offer free/discounted admission\tCitywide participating venues\thttps://www.timeout.com/newyork/museums/free-museum-days-in-nyc\tFREE or Pay-What-You-Wish (5-8pm)\tCheck specific museum websites for participating venues each month\tExtended evening hours, less crowded than daytime, socializing opportunity, cultural access\tFirst Friday of every month, 5-8pm\tYES - social museum outing\t2-3 hours\tINPUT: First Friday of month + list of participating museums REQUEST OUTPUT: FREE or pay-what-you-wish museum admission (5-8pm window) BUDGET-FRIENDLY UNDER $15\tNew York Public Library Events (Teen Programs)\tFree/low-cost author talks, teen book clubs, creative workshops hosted by NYPL branches\tMultiple branch locations citywide\thttps://www.nypl.org/\tFREE (some donations accepted)\tCheck NYPL.org calendar for teen events at your local branch\tLiterary events, workshops, book discussions, author meet-ups, creative writing, safe teen community\tYear-round (check branch calendar)\tYES - group-friendly\t1-2 hours\tINPUT: Teen interest in books/writing + local library branch REQUEST OUTPUT: Free or low-cost event attendance + author/creative workshop access BUDGET-FRIENDLY UNDER $15\tNYC Parks Recreation Centers - Teen Activities\tMultiple free/low-cost sports, arts, gaming activities at neighborhood rec centers\tCitywide (every neighborhood)\thttps://www.nycgovparks.org/programs/recreation/teens\tFREE to $10 (varies by activity)\tRegister at local rec center OR online\tBasketball, volleyball, arts classes, video games, tutoring, leadership programs, safe teen space\tYear-round programming\tYES - community-based\tOngoing\tINPUT: Local rec center + activity preference REQUEST OUTPUT: Free or low-cost activity enrollment + access to rec center facilities BUDGET-FRIENDLY UNDER $20\tImprov Comedy Classes (Budget Options)\tUpright Citizens Brigade offers affordable workshops/classes for teens interested in comedy\tEast Village\thttps://ucbcomedy.com/\t$15-20 per class (check website for youth rates)\tOnline registration required\tLearn improv skills, perform with peers, creative outlet, fun group activity, build confidence\tOngoing schedule (register in ad"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=2e79e79d-f636-46ef-a835-c7798d328296","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=2e79e79d-f636-46ef-a835-c7798d328296"}]}]}]
